<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Existing homeowners have overtaken first-time buyers as the biggest source of demand in the housing market. </p>

<p>Online estate agent Zoopla said the change had resulted from the coronavirus pandemic as younger families had been increasingly shut out by lenders. </p>

<p>Changing landscape: Zoopla's latest house-price index found demand from homeowners looking to move had risen 48 per cent over the first three months of this year</p>

<p>Zoopla's latest house-price index found demand from homeowners looking to move had risen 48 per cent over the first three months of this year. </p>

<p>Demand from first-time buyers was up 11 per cent – the first time since 2017 that first-time buyers had not been the biggest driver.</p>
